name: GetEventsResult

fields.name: eventBatch
fields.documentation: The batch of events returned for the requested aggregate.

fields.name: lastSequenceNumber
fields.documentation:
The sequence number of the last event included in this batch.

This is useful for paging and requesting the next batch of events.

fields.name: requestId
fields.documentation: A unique identifier that correlates this result with its {@link GetEvents} request.

fields.name: timestamp
fields.documentation: Timestamp at which this result was generated.

methods.name: toMetric
methods.documentation:
Converts this result to a minimal metric object for performance logging or monitoring.

This avoids logging full event payloads while preserving key metadata. @return a metric summary of the response
